President Cyril Ramaphosa is attending the G7 Summit. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa says Africa is in need of support for infrastructure development. He says the continent needs partners who will cement and consolidate what African countries are doing. READ: Ramaphosa says working for the people of SA his 'top priority' Ramaphosa was speaking at the G7 Summit in France. “We need to get ready for these wonderful developments in Africa...the important one for me is infrastructure development...we need to unlock all that.” Ramaphosa was invited to this year's G7 Summit by France President, Emmanuel Macron. The summit will seek to develop and enhance a partnership with Africa.